{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Line a large baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and lightly grease paper. Place tomato, onion (cut side down) and garlic onto it. Drizzle with olive oil, ½ teaspoon of the salt and 1 teaspoon of the oregano and roast for 2 hours (160°C). Remove from oven and set aside.","Place chillies into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>2 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, then chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add carrot, celery, capsicum and coriander (optional) and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add ghee and cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add cumin, paprika, remaining 1 tsp salt and remaining 2 tsp oregano, then cook <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Once cool enough to handle, carefully remove skin from garlic. Add garlic, roasted tomato and roasted onion to mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add all remaining ingredients and cook <nobr>10-15 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr> or until beans are cooked to your liking","Season to taste, then serve molè garnished with shaved chocolate."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 tbsp extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing","5 vine-ripened tomatoes, cut into halves","2 red onions, cut into halves","4 garlic cloves, skins on","1 ½ tsp sea salt, plus extra for seasoning","3 tsp dried oregano","1 - 2 fresh long red chillies, cut into halves and deseeded, if preferred","1 carrot, cut into quarters","1 celery stalk, trimmed and cut into quarters","½ red capsicum, cut into halves and deseeded","4 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only (optional)","50 g ghee","2 tsp ground cumin","3 tsp smoked paprika","800 g canned black beans, rinsed and drained (approx. 480 g after draining)","2 tsp balsamic vinegar","2 tsp Rapadura sugar","50 g tomato paste","2 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","50 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa), grated, plus extra shaved for garnishing","250 g filtered water"]}],"id":"r152663","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-TUc-yWJNXyU\/XZVRXY8pBZI\/AAAAAAAAdNc\/517H1qvMsWYEpIO9fLbNDdcCCmgFHfdJACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_myByrqneXz-dz8vI.png","title":"Black bean molè (black bean chocolate chilli)","publishedAt":"2017-06-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.9 g","fat":"21.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"26.5 g","calories":"1510 kJ \/ 359 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, large baking tray, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Everyday Cookbook <\/em>for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","Serve molè with sour cream, rice and\/or tortillas.","This recipe is easily made dairy free by using dairy free chocolate and olive oil instead of ghee.","This recipe was originally printed in Jo Whitton's book, <em>Quirky Cooking<\/em>."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","2h 25m","6 portions"]}